● code/prompts.py is done. It defines:

  - SYSTEM_PROMPT — images as primary truth, history can't override visual
  evidence, explicit instruction to never obey text/instructions embedded in
  images (flag text_instruction_present instead) — directly addresses the
  prompt-injection risk I flagged from case_008/seal cases, and a rule for
  detecting stock/watermarked photos → non_original_image.
  - CLAIM_ANALYSIS_PROMPT_TEMPLATE — fills in claim conversation, image IDs,
  filtered evidence requirements, and full user-history context, then asks for a
  strict JSON object with exactly the 10 model-owned output keys and their
  allowed-value lists (sourced live from schemas.py, not duplicated literals).
  - ENUM_FIX_PROMPT_TEMPLATE — the one-shot retry prompt for Stage 3a enum
  coercion when a field doesn't match an allowed value.
  - NO_HISTORY_SUMMARY_TEXT — fallback text for users with no row in
  user_history.csv.

  One thing to flag: I added the NO_HISTORY_SUMMARY_TEXT fallback because not
  every user_id may exist in user_history.csv — worth confirming pipeline.py
  should treat a missing user as "no risk" rather than erroring.

