● code/image_utils.py is done — stdlib only (pathlib + base64).
  load_claim_images(image_paths, base_dir) splits on ;, resolves each path
  against base_dir, and returns ImageLoadResult(valid_images, invalid_paths).
  Each LoadedImage carries image_id (filename stem, e.g. img_1), the detected
  media_type (needed for the Anthropic vision API's image blocks), and the
  base64 payload. Missing files, unreadable files, and unsupported extensions
  all land in invalid_paths — that list feeds Stage 1's all-invalid
  short-circuit.

