  vlm_client, pipeline, post_hoc) compile cleanly.

  What it does:
  - Enum coercion: normalize → check membership → one model-fix retry
  (_request_fix, reusing call_vlm with images=[]) → fall back to the per-field
  default in DEFAULT_NOT_ENOUGH_INFO. object_part validates against the right
  subset for the claim's claim_object.
  - Logical consistency: valid_image=false ⟹ evidence_standard_met=false;
  evidence_standard_met=false ⟹ claim_status can't be supported (forced to
  not_enough_information). The contradicted→none rule was intentionally dropped
  per your earlier call.
  - Extra guard I added: supporting_image_ids is hard-restricted to image IDs
  that were actually loaded — a model can't cite an image that doesn't exist.
  - History risk merge: adds user_history_risk when past_claim_count > 5,
  rejected_claim > 0, or history_flags is non-empty/non-none, deduped.

